ce:section.ce:para:
The findings showed that rates of photodegradation increases as in PAN-TiQD than PAN because of presence of TiQD which due to the photocatalytic activity of TiQD supported on nano PAN which increase the active site during the photodegradation process. Recently, PAN has shown great potential as a photosensitizer conducting polymers because of their particular properties such as π-*π transition and low band gap which the electron can be excited from HOMO level to LUMO level [18,80–82]. Really, PAN had attracted much attention for its distinguishable properties such as cheap monomer, good environmental stability, high conductivity, and ease of preparation. Also, doping of PAN with TiQD led to lowered the band gap value and shifted the optical response at the visible light region [39,40]. In Fig. 7
                         (a, b, c and d), the photodegradation rate of dye with PAN-TiQD is (kapp = 5.13 × 10-3 s−1) and higher than nano PAN (kapp = 2.34 × 10-3s−1) while it is (kapp = 17.01 × 10-3 s−1) for TiQD (Scheme 2
                        ).
